=Evaluate this LinkedIn prospect for outbound DM outreach:

Name: {{$json.Person}}
Role: {{$json.Role}}
Company: {{$json.Company}}
Country: {{$json.Country}}

Return ONLY this JSON:
{
  "lead_score": "Hot | Warm | Cold",
  "priority": "High | Medium | Low",
  "message_angle": "pain_point | value_add | curiosity | social_proof",
  "score_reason": "one sentence max"
}

parameters.jsCode:
return items.map(item => {
  const raw =
    item.json.output?.[0]?.content?.find(c => c.type === 'output_text')?.text ||
    item.json.output?.[0]?.content?.[0]?.text ||
    '{}';

  let parsed = {};
  try { parsed = JSON.parse(raw); } catch(e) { parsed = {}; }

  return {
    json: {
      ...item.json,
      AI_LeadScore: parsed.lead_score || 'Warm',
      AI_Priority: parsed.priority || 'Medium',
      AI_MessageAngle: parsed.message_angle || 'value_add',
      AI_ScoreReason: parsed.score_reason || ''
    }
  };
});

values.content:
=Write a cold LinkedIn DM for this prospect.

Name: {{$json.Person}}
Role: {{$json.Role}}
Company: {{$json.Company}}
Message angle: {{$json.AI_MessageAngle}}

Rules:
- Max 3 short lines
- No 'I hope this finds you well'
- No generic openers
- End with one soft conversational question
- Sound natural, not salesy

Output ONLY the DM text.

parameters.jsCode:
return items.map(item => {
  const text =
    item.json.output?.[0]?.content?.find(c => c.type === 'output_text')?.text ||
    item.json.output?.[0]?.content?.[0]?.text ||
    `Hi ${item.json.Person}, noticed your work at ${item.json.Company} — had a quick question for you.`;

  return {
    json: {
      ...item.json,
      AI_FirstDM: text.trim()
    }
  };
});

